reviews: My wife and I had just over a day and a half in Paris at the end of our France trip before returning to the USA, so we were looking for a location that was fairly central to the sites that were most important to us. Hotel Passy Eiffel met those needs! Check in was super easy, and staff made arrangements for our taxi to CDG in two days. Our room was small but comfortable. It even featured air conditioning. The breakfast was only ok - the breakfast room was crammed with people and the choices were not plentiful. But hotel location was the most important for us - right after check in, we walked to lunch right around the corner, and then thru the Trocadero and its beautiful Eiffel Tower views up Avenue Kleber to the Arc de Triomphe. From there we walked down the Champs Elysees toward to Place de la Concorde, and across the Seine in front of the Eiffel Tower. Location of the hotel was important as we had Saturday night dinner cruise reservations and Bateaux Parisiens was only a 15 minute walk away. The Passy Metro station is only 5 minutes away, as are numerous cafes and bakeries. Hotel Passy Eiffel was a solid choice and not overly touristy.

My husband and I are on our honeymoon! We stayed here in Paris and were so thankful for the excellent customer service we received by everyone at Hotel Passy. The location was perfect, right around the corner from the Eiffel Tower and we even walked to the Louve Museum. If you’re looking for a friendly and clean place to stay with a view stay here.

This hotel is ideal for a short city break. It’s within 7 minutes walk of the Eiffel Tower and a few minutes to Passy metro station.

The hotel itself is spotlessly clean, provides a good breakfast to get you on your way each day and has a friendly team of staff. The staff were great; nothing was any trouble to them.

The rooms are compact and ideal for a short city break.

My wife and I reserved several rooms for ourselves and some relations. We could not have made a better choice. The rooms, though small as expected in Paris, were just as pictured. The room we had was so quiet and the comfortable bed made for great sleeping. The staff could not have been more accomodating and helpful and the location is absolutely perfect for getting around. The St.Paul neighborhood is great for exploring and has absolutely every amenity. We will definitely be back.

The hotel was quaint and very clean. Located incredibly close to the Eiffel Tower. The hotel is near clothing shops and supermarket within walking distance. There is a lovely pastry shop two doors down, a pharmacy right next door and a restaurant on the corner. There is a wine shop directly across from the hotel. Centrally located.

This a nice hotel with good value for the money. And the location is super. It was a bit hot during the night but I didn’t check for air-condition or any other regulation of the temperature so I might blame my self for that

Quality = good. To be better: a little bit noisy breakfast (in the kitchen - with the door open always), little space in the breakfast room - and a bit more generosity always helps (ordering a cup of tea or coffee costs money - nothing for free here... ) But - it should be mentioned: reception is doing a good job. They help you with a taxi etc.

My family and I stayed 4 nights. Great location - enjoyed the close proximity to the Eiffel Tower, especially for evening strolls to admire the lights. The room and lobby were lovely and inviting. Hair dryer was a bit outdated but still did the job. The checkout staff was pleasant and very helpful in allowing us to store our luggage until we departed for the airport. I would recommend and definitely return.

We had a fantastic family room which suited us and our 8 year old perfectly. The room was immaculate, the hotel was quiet and the staff very friendly and helpful. Excellent location near lovely places to eat, good shops and attractions.
Charming Boutique hotel with 48 rooms. Breakfast buffet served daily for an additional charge. Close to shopping and restaurants. Very safe area. Short 5 to 10 minute walk to Eiffel Tower. Have fun!

We had an amazing stay at Passy Hotel. Very nice staff, good atmosphare, Lovely rooms, beds and the breakfast was good. The hotel location was very central.
Close to shopping, restaurants, cafes, metro and typical tourist activities. The trust bar was a smart and Funny thing!

Fantastic spot in the 16th district! Clean, quiet and so welcoming, the Passy Eiffel was the perfect location for my stay. You can walk to main attractions like the Trocadéro and Eiffel Tower, but also within close proximity to wonderful shops, the Monet Museum and Bois de Boulogne. I stayed in multiple neighborhoods during my first trip to Paris and Passy was such an amazing place. The hotel was welcoming, charming and I couldn’t have asked for a better stay.

What a great first experience in Paris. Staff was friendly and helpful. Everything was very clean. The location was ideal for me, a 5 min walk to the metro and a ten minute walk to Trocadéro. I highly recommend the steak at Le Passy just a few doors down. Les Bistrot des Vignes a few blocks away was also phenomenal.

Very nice hotel. Room and Bathroom spacious for European standards.updated bathroom fixtures. Friendly staff, Convenient location - walking distance to the Eiffel Tower. Quick Uber pick-ups. Typical European breakfast. Comfortable bed with nice linens and towels Overall a nice stay for a great value.

I absolutely loved this hotel! It’s everything you need if you want to stay somewhere off the beaten path of large chain hotels. It’s cute with a ton of character and walking distance to landmarks, easy walk to the Seine, Eiffel Tower, Monet museum, Trocadéro, etc. There are tons of shopping and cafes around the area also in all directions! The rooms are small but literally have everything you need for a comfortable stay. The beds are comfortable, bedding is soft and clean. The area is quiet at night, we slept with the windows open every night and it was perfect. I would 100% stay here again. The staff is great, every kind and helpful. The honesty bar is genius and really made it easy to just grab a glass of wine on our way to the room. I loved every thing about this hotel.

Great stay, no problems. This was my first trip back to Paris after COVID and it was nice that they remembered me from before. Breakfasts were good, and staff helpful and efficient. will keep coming back here.

Room rate was quite expensive but I had to accept because accomodations in Paris is generally expensive. (especially the room rates in Paris during our stay was exceptionally expensive). However, the room I stayed was small but cozy and clean(single room). The room was cleaned everyday and staffs were all very kind. However, there were no refrigerator in my room. I heard that my colleague who stayed in classic double room had fridge in his room. Breakfast was very nice, although it was not so fancy, I really enjoyed it(I had breakfasts everyday - three days). It was very close to Eiffel and I could see the Eiffel tower from my room. Although my room was on the street side outside noises never disturbed me because it was located in a quiet area. It was a good choice for my business trip.

Great hotel. Near tour eiffel, it is a calm neighborhood, with restaurants, stores. Clean rooms, service is good, good for family. It is a good place to stay when tou don’t want a very busy neighborhood

An incredible gem of a hotel that is small but cosy and convenient. Within a 5-minute walk to Metro Passy Station (Line 6) and a small grocery market (Monoprix), a 10-15 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower (need to cross a bridge), and right next to a wonderful bakery selling sandwiches and all sorts of tempting sweet pastries! Staff was amazing helping me contact the restaurant where we had dinner the night before to inquire about a lost beanie (found!). Room was just the right temperature for sleeping on those cold mid-January nights during the week we spent in Paris.

We really liked our room. It had a very comfortable bed and the deluxe room had a great amount of room for two people for three days. Bathroom was quite small, but still comfortable, and had a good sized shower. Only a 13 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower and each night we did a short walk to get good nights views of it. Staff were also helpful in booking us a morning taxi to the airport and taking our bags out

The hotel was in a great location, close to major attractions, an amazing bakery and lots of restaurants. Also close to Metro stops which was great. We stayed in a triple room which was quite large by Parisian standards and was great. Lugging suitcases up and down the final flight of stairs from the 5th to 6th floor wasn't great but understandable due to the buildings age. The staff were friendly enough although the older lady on reception when asked if she could recommend a restaurant for New Years Eve dinner was not really helpful at all, only gave one suggestion that was not really close and didn't offer to make a reservation for us either, we ended up finding a great restaurant much closer ourselves. The man at checkout, albeit at 6am in the morning was a bit surly also.

I would not recommend this hotel to anyone, first off the staff are so rude and not helpful. We booked a room with a view but when we arrived the said that our room was cancelled but “luckily” the had another room which was not as nice available … basically sold our room again and gave us a crappy room at the same price..

Very nice physical building in a convenient location, close to Passy metro stop and in a pleasant neighborhood. Breakfast room was a bit tight, and that is the the only criticism I can make. The rooms were spotless and the beds comfortable. The staff were friendly and excellent in English, which helps when one is not so good in French.We will certainly stay here again if the opportunity presents itself.

Excellent , thanks for everything
The location be great,very close to restaurants and every part of the city you want to visit .
If you are not with car you need do 5 min to the station… the personal be nice and very friendly

Hôtel Passy Eiffel was a delight for our trip to Paris. The front desk staff was always very friendly and were able to accommodate our early arrival. Our room was clean, beautifully designed, and had a balcony with a view of the Eiffel Tower. The location was perfect to explore the cute area of Passy and easy to get to all public transportation. We would love to stay here again and would recommend to all.

A the room was very little. The bed was bad. But overall it was clean and cozy so. The price is too high for this room size. At least we saw the eiffel tower from our balcany. The breakfast was not bad.

A small-size and excellent place for a short visit to Paris. Very clean, well-located and staff were helpful and pleasant. Maybe a little expensive, but this is the general case in Paris. Cosy environment with some outdoor options. We are quite satisfied with our experience in this hotel, and consider to come again next visits.

The Passy Eiffel Hotel has excellent service, and the room was clean and well-equipped. The reception officers were polite and on disposal. The breakfast offer is not diversified enough, and the restaurant is tiny and uncomfortable. However, the location and room comfort are perfect.

The Passy Eiffel Hotel was a great place to stay for our first visit. It was near a metro entrance, great cafes, a delicious bakery and a view of the Eiffel Tower. The staff were friendly, the rooms clean, and the beds were comfortable. There was an elevator but it was very tiny and we had to take two trips to get our luggage upstairs for the four of us.

Location very good - nice area to be in the evening and for shopping in day if that is your thing. Easy to get to main Museums. We visited Musee Marmottan Monet and Balzac House which are a walk and excellent. Room basic for the price, but largely comfortable, good shower, some road noice but not too bad. Staff helpful. Honesty bar good idea, but drinks were not cold and no water provided in rooms.

We hate leaving bad reviews. We usually just don’t review at all. But after being lied to, we’ve just had enough. The hotel is cute enough. But that’s where it stops for our trip. We were told we had a room with a view. That’s being awfully generous. Just because you can stick your head out a window and see the Eiffel Tower, it doesn’t mean you have a room with a view. They oversold that, but weren’t too bothered by it. We were in Paris, after all. We were excited to be here.

Next, we open up the cabinet that houses the fridge to find it doesn’t work. After that, mildew in the bathroom along with a shower head that doesn’t work. It’s a combo shower head, and only one part of it works. Next the bed is hard as a rock. Like sleeping on a cheap futon. We don’t expect Tempurpedic mattresses at hotels and firmness is a preference, certainly, but unless you like sleeping on rocks, it’s not all that comfortable. Still, we persevered. Nothing was going to ruin this trip for us. The location is fantastic and we enjoyed the restaurants and cafes nearby. Plus, bonus, they have A/C.

I know, I know, it’s fall/winter in Paris. Who needs A/C? Well, we do. We prefer it to be cold when we sleep at night. Ice cold. And more than anything, we specifically booked this room because the hotel told us they had A/C. It’s plastered all over the website. So, the first night, the A/C worked like a charm. Kept the room cold and we slept ok, despite the rock hard beds. We come back from doing all the touristy things people do their first few nights in Paris to a scorchingly hot room. We thought, we’ll just turn the A/C on. But wait! The A/C won’t turn on. “What’s going on,” we thought. After a trip downstairs to speak to someone at the front desk, we were informed they shut the A/C off completely, throughout the whole building. What!? When pressed further, the gentleman at the front desk tells us that the A/C had been off for two weeks. THIS was clearly a lie. We had A/C just the night before. When called out, he quickly changes his story to it was left on by mistake. Well, why didn’t you just say that? Why lie to us? There was zero point to it. And to top it off, he tells us to just open the window. As if that’s a reasonable fix. It’s not. Why? Because our room is on a noisy street. Also, because you advertise you have A/C. If you turn the A/C off building wide, you don’t have A/C. And now you are just guilty of false advertising!

And that was the straw that broke the camel’s back, so to say. We couldn’t ignore the issues any longer. And we HATE being lied to. That’s the quickest way to get us to tell the world about all the flaws in your establishment. So yeah, I’m telling you, the reader of this, don’t book this hotel expecting there to be working A/C, a working fridge, a working shower, or anything else. As a matter of fact, don’t book this hotel. It’s not the one you are looking for.

Great place to stay in Paris! We stayed 4 nights. The front desk personnel were wonderful, housekeeping great, the hotel was spotless and the location was wonderful!! We walked every evening after dinner to see the Eiffel Tower. There are many cafes and restaurants. The side streets had wonderful bakeries and a great place to get lunch. We recommend the Hop on Hop off bus tour and the swine river cruise . It lets us explore so much of Paris and added to my photo collection. This was our 2nd trip, looking forward to returning next December and of course staying at the Hotel Passy Eiffel!!

We stayed in this lovely boutique hotel this past week. Wonderful location, great shops and restaurants close by, easy walk to the Eiffel Tower. rooms are compact, but very comfortable, bathrooms and showers are a good size. Staff was super helpful and always welcoming. Would highly recommend!

We stated here for our honeymoon and they were able to provide us a room with a beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower and our own balcony. We spent some time every evening with a drink on the balcony and loved watching the buzz of the night life go by. The rooms were cosy and very accommodating, nothing was too much trouble to ask. I loved the idea of the honesty bar and breakfast was really lovely. We will definitely stay here again!

This is a wonderful boutique hotel in a great location in walking distance to restaurants, Eiffel Tower, metro and water taxi. The rooms are compact which we expected however they were very comfortable with good beds and showers etc. The hotel had a nice courtyard and comfortable guest areas for lounging including the “honesty bar”. Front desk staff was very helpful with restaurant suggestions and directions. Very clean and great value. We would definitely stay here again.

From the moment we walked through the doors of the hotel, we knew we'd struck the jackpot. The receptionist was charming and very helpful. The communal areas very welcoming with modern styling and the rooms well equipped and comfortable. What we hadn't expected was the amazing shops and restaurants right on the door step. A real Gem of a find

Would recommend! Close to metro. Easy access to restaurants and shops. Booking, check in and check out was easy process. Staff was pleasant. Rooms are lovely and view from was a dream!! Plan to visit again!

I was very happy with my choice to stay at the Hotel Passy Eiffel. The location in a residential area and on a nice shopping street, close to several metro stops, the Seine, and the Eiffel tower was perfect. Lots of places to walk around and to eat. The hotel itself is charming and clean, and very quiet, with typically Parisian-sized rooms. I would definitely stay there again!

Our room was very nice and surprisingly spacious. We had daily maid service so the room was kept very clean. We enjoyed the breakfast bar and found it to be very nice.
The location was just blocks from the Eiffel Tower so we were able to walk there. The neighborhood itself was nice with many cafes and shopping nearby.
We would stay at the Passy Eiffel Hotel again and recommend it to others.

Stayed at this hotel for a few nights while in Paris and definitely recommend! The location is great, only about a 10-15 min walk to the Eiffel Tower, and many close restaurants and a bakery two doors down! The hotel itself was clean, the staff were friendly and helpful, and the room was a decent size.

We stayed for a few nights and we were very impressed with the cleanliness, the location as and the friendly staff. A very stylish, boutique hotel in a great location. The hotel has a unique ambience that is very welcoming.

I am just home from a long weekend stay here. It’s a lovely hotel within a short distance from many lovely sights. Breakfast was delicious.
The staff were courteous and helpful. Our rooms were small but spotless. I definitely would return here.

My wife and I stayed at the Passy Eiffel Hotel during our Paris Vacation. The location is absolutely perfect. The staff is wonderful and were extremely helpful with any questions we had. The breakfast in the morning was everything you could ask for. Our room overlooked the Eiffel Tower if you opened the window. The area around the hotel is really safe and just down the block from the Passy Metro Station. It was about a 15 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower right along the Seine River. Highly recommend this hotel for your next stay in Paris.

Hotel Passy Eiffel had a perfect location, only a 10 minute walk to the Eiffel tower, close to restaurants and shopping. It was a comfortable, clean neighborhood. The staff was terrific, Muriele at the front desk had a sunny disposition, and was kind and helpful. I would recommend staying here!

We just came back from a 5 days Paris girls trip and this hotel is a gem. I would describe as cozy, charming and the sense of home away from home. The location was also a key factor on our decision as it’s literally 2 min from the metro Passy (where you can go anywhere from here) and 5-7 min from the Eiffel Tower which honestly nothing else should be required. After a long day walking on the beautiful streets of Paris we would go back, shower, relax and then grab a bottle of champagne and go to the Eiffel Tower as you can sit down at the stairs, listening to live music overlooking at the tower. This is our first time here and we will definitely go back with our families to the same hotel. The breakfast was amazing with simple things that we all love: great assortment of cheese, plain and chocolate croissants, yogurt, eggs, orange juice, amazing coffee, I miss that so much. The staff are nice and always smiling and willing to help. The shower was great and so the beds. Also, they are 2-3 min from a nice mall which has a supermarket (Metropix) underground so we were able to save on food right there. Right at the corner of the hotel there is a great and affordable place to eat super recommend (their salmon is to die for and only paid EUR 19). We could also see the Eiffel Tower from our room. Merci Passy Eiffel e a bientot.

Overall was not bad to stay in passy eiffel hotel. But the location was a bit too far from the center, not so easy to find a nearby cafes and restaurants. The people was friendly and nice. I had a room in the roof, so I had to take the lift and then one more floor with the stair. It was not comfortable. I didn't expect that.

Decided to stay at this location after reading many reviews. I highly recommend it. I found the staff to be very nice and my room was very clean and quiet. We stayed in a superior room which had a queen bed.
The Eiffel Tower is a 15 minute walk down hill from the hotel. We never ate the continental breakfast at 14 euro per person because there is a outstanding pastry shop 3 doors down called Desgranges. I did get coffee every morning and brought it back to the room. To the left of Desgranges at the corner is a nice bar where you can sit, have a drink and watch the people stroll by. To the right and up the hill about 10 minutes is Aero Passy Restaurant which has a really good omelette. This hotel is also near the Metro and local shopping. It is a local neighborhood so don't expect large crowds or name brand stores here.

The hotel was fantastic! Only a 10 min walk to the Eiffel Tower and had plenty of restaurants around! The staff were lovely and very welcoming. The beds were so comfy and we had a great nights sleep! Can’t fault this hotel. We will definitely come back in the future!

Great location, near the Eiffel Tower! Some of the rooms have a view of the Eiffel Tower too😊. Walking distance from many sites too. Clean rooms, comfortable beds. Nice garden area inside the courtyard for smoking or relaxing. Excellent staff! They were very helpful.

We loved staying at the Passy Eiffel Hotel! It is a beautiful hotel with A/C in a romantic city with a great location! Service was great, the room was clean, and the staff was very nice! We would definitely recommend this hotel to any couple staying to Paris!

Great location, walking distance to the tower, Seine, and metro, yet surprisingly peaceful. Rooms were clean, contained everything we needed, including air con, and beds were very comfortable. Lovely showers.

Passy Eiffel Hotel was as cute as I'd hoped for! I was staying with a friend and we got a room with twin beds. I was delighted to get a room where we could step out of our window into our own private little balcony with two chairs and a view of the top of the Eiffel Tower!

Room included a small fridge. The staff was friendly and spoke English. It was a 10 min walk to the Eiffel Tower! Very safe area with a bakery right next door. AC worked great!

Only downside was the very tiny elevator. It worked fine! And the hotel wasn't ever busy enough that we had to wait for it, but it could only take two people or a single person and their luggage at a time. However, it was in fine working order.

Definitely recommend!

Great hotel!!! The best hotel we could have booked. Located in a safe neighborhood, close to boulangeries, restaurants, Trocadero, Tour Eiffel, Passy Metro Station, FranPrix (minimarket).
For breakfast they served the BEST CROISSANTS in all Paris, good quality cheeses, hams and other goodies. The staff was friendly, kind and helpfull, always made us feel welcome and taken care off.
The rooms were beautifully decorated, spacious, clean, great beds and had windows that you could open to let the fresh air come in. We would choose Passy Eiffel Hotel over and over again!!!

Unfortunately our stay was cut short due to airline delays and cancelations. This hotel is very cute and in a wonderful location. The staff was very nice and helpful. We had a cute little room that was accessed through the outdoor garden.

Hotel Passy Eiffel is really lovely--it's so close to the Eiffel Tower and the 16th in general is a very nice and quiet area. The rooms are small, but more than comfortable. The staff is also friendly and accommodating.

Lovely hotel located in the heart of Passy. Stayed there for two nights and found it really good value. Staff was very service minded and helpful. Room was good size for Paris. Can only recommend this hotel.

We stayed here for 5 days in late June 22.

Staff: friendly and helpful

Rooms: small but this seemed to be the theme around France. Well appointed and clean. We had a view of the Eiffel Tower from our window which was nice.

Location: Excellent. 10-15 min walk to the Eiffel tower, 1 min to cafes and hotels for coffee, food and drinks. Local Patisseries - yum!

I had an amazing stay at the hotel. They gave me my dream trip to Paris. It is close to attractions, restaurants, and shopping. I even had a clear view of the Eiffel Tower from my hotel room. I had many great meals right in Passy. I was able to walk to the Eiffel Tower. I took the nearby metro to visit other sites in Paris. The reception is very helpful, friendly, and welcoming. They helped make arrangements for other travel around France. The hotel itself is very charming. The breakfast was a perfect way to begin my day. The area that the hotel is located in is very safe.

Just had an excellent stay at the Plassey Eiffel, I was there for work and from the start it was a very enjoyable stay. The rooms were clean and comfortable and the staff were excellent. Would definitely stay there again.

I booked early for 3 nights and found this to be a nice value in Paris. The hotel is convenient to the metro, some restaurants/shops, and an easy walk to the Eiffel Tower. The staff was pleasant and the room was always very clean. If you truly eat breakfast, I also found the breakfast to be a decent value, especially once discovering just how terribly expensive Paris can be. Although it was fine for us, note the some rooms are quite small. Overall I’d stay here again.

Passy Eiffel Hotel was in a great location, rooms lovely and staff were great. would stay there again. They also helped organise our transfers from the train station to their hotel, and our communication with them before we arrived was always prompt and a great help.

We loved Hotel Passy Eiffel! Our room was perfect...was so quiet and peaceful. We especially loved the courtyard, especially in the evenings after a long day of sightseeing. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Location was perfect...3 minutes to metro, and 10 minutes to the tower. I look forward to staying again!

Perfect location, spotless little gem, very comfy beds, very quiet, well decorated, no fuss straight forward hotel, very helpful staff. Loved the little decor items in the rooms which makes it seem warm and personal. The only tiny missing thing was no body lotion amongst the toiletries, so I had to buy one. Also the courtyard was not in use (as in no breakfast is served there) and that was a shame.

Excellent location! Nice hotel! View of Eiffel Tower from our window. Staff was excellent , very courteous . I would definitely stay there again on a future trip . Wonderful restaurants around and easy to get to metro

Not too happy with this hotel after reading all the good reviews about this place. Room was not cleaned one day and other occasions the bath/shower looked dirtier then when it was left. The location of the hotel is good and there is a nice view of the Eiffel Tower. Shops are close and nearby and metro is also a close walk from hotel. Do not recommend the garden rooms as it can get very loud on the bottom floor and unpleasant noises coming from above.

We came here on a 4 day layover vacation - found the hotel super fast and booked it and we were very glad we did it. Location is amazing 10 min walk from eiffel tower and 20 min walk from everything else you might wanna see. If you wanna go somewhere further its 15-20 min uber to everywhere. Breakfast is good in a hotel (14 euro ) per person but we wanted to explore the neighborhood and we did. Amazing sushi next to a hotel and great breakfast spots as well. Bed was comfy - room was small but no need for more - shower was epic relaxing. Will come back here again. Front desk was very polite and service great.

My spouse and I came here for our anniversary trip, and it took us a while to find a hotel that was reasonable for our budget, but also nice and centrally located. I'm happy to say that this hotel hit that perfect sweet spot! I'm sure you can imagine my excitement when we got to room 21 and realized our room had 2 french balcony windows with a view of the top of the Eiffel tower! The location was great - about a 2-minute walk to the metro and about a 10-minute walk to the Eiffel tower. There were many shops, bakeries, and restaurants close by, and we had a very smooth experience checking in and out (booked through Expedia). The decor was fun and fresh, and while it could feel a bit small in the elevator and halls, I felt that added to this boutique hotel's charm and I felt the room was a good size. The bathroom was clean and had all the amenities you would expect as well. After a wonderful week in Paris, I can't wait to come back, and I would definitely stay here again!

I very much enjoyed my stay at Passy Eiffel Hotel. My room was perfect, the service was excellent, and I enjoyed the breakfast! Easy access to the metro, and plenty of walkable places to explore. The street is adorable as well. I will choose this place every time.

Our room was awesome (updated) and clean. Good enough size (for Paris). We had a balcony with a view of the Eiffel (at least the upper half of the Eiffel) which we did not know if we would get to have until we got there. It was our 40th Anniversary and we couldn't have asked for a better experience. Marie at the desk was the best and very accommodating. Best value in the world!!!

We had to pay breakfast TWICE. I booked with booking.com but it was cancelled due to problems with our irish card. Fee, booked 2 months earlier, had it included, but we had to pay through a different channel Passy did not considered that and charge us the breakfast AGAIN, even though I tried to explain, I was totally ignored. On top of that, WE DID NOT EVEN have breakfast, since we had to leave early for the airport and no take away was facilitated. Would never go back to this hotel. And do not stay in room 3, you have the light sensor in the corridor going on and off all night and you can hear it, so annoying.

Rooms are a bit small and pretty basic but you can't beat the price for this location. You can walk to the Eiffel and the Seine. Staff is friendly and helpful. Parking in the mall area is the easiest.

I stayed in this hotel before, the location is perfect right in the middle of a shopping street and few minutes walk to Passy metro station and 15 min walk to Tour Eiffel.
My room had a nice view overlooking the street, it can get a bit noisy if you open the window but I wasn't bothered. The hotel is calm with a nice lobby. I didn't try the breakfast though.
All in all I enjoyed my stay and would definitely come back again.

The hotel was in a great location. We enjoy walking anyway but everywhere we wanted to go was within an easy walk.; about 10-15 minutes to the Eiffel Tower about 1 hour to the Louvre. The hotel itself was clean with friendly helpful staff. The courtyard was a lovely addition, it was lovely to sit outside in the morning or the early evening with a drink. Rooms were well equipped. We would certainly book there again if we were to return to Paris.

Receptionist was very unpleasant and rude my whole stay, didn’t feel welcome. Took 2 days to get an iron, I was charged for breakfast even though I cancelled prior ( and I was told I could) I do not recommend at all, there are way to many hotels in the area to settle for this one. Poor.

We just spend 2 night in Passy Eiffel Hotel and we must say it was all perfect. Very nice, small hotel with friendly staff,and good servive. If you are looking for a clean nice place to spend a great time in Paris for a fair price, I would recommend Passy Eiffel Hotel.

I stayed here for 3 nights on my own. Great location, wonderful staff, and I felt very safe. Within walking distance from the Eiffel Tower and metro station. Very clean and exactly what I needed. Much better than I expected for a 3 star hotel in Paris. They offer a breakfast for 14 euros but I didn’t take them up on that.

The staff was amazing, the location was perfect. Local coffee/bars and walking distance to Eiffel tower.Always felt safe. Would definitely come back again. The room was clean and the bed was really comfortable.

We stayed at this hotel for 6 days in May 2022. Place was unique, our room was well equipped and spacious. Only issue was the reception told us the AC was not working. However, we found out after two days later the AC did work. We had slept with windows ajar at night, so there was a lot of street noise. However, with the windows closed there was almost no sound/noise from the street. Also, we did not purchase breakfast at the hotel, a little too expensive for us but we made the error of bringing the bakery goods from the bakery next door into the breakfast room, which upset the staff. Minor issue. Place was so close to the Eiffel Tower, I was able to see it every night from my room. I would definitely stay at the us hotel again and again.

My wife and I stayed here on vacation and we really enjoyed our stay. It’s a charming and romantic hotel with a great breakfast. Also it’s a short walk from the Eiffel Tower and subway entrance. We would definitely stay here again!

My husband and I have traveled to Paris a few times, staying at a new hotel each time. Passy Eiffel Hotel is a perfect location, steps from a metro, walking distance from the Eiffel Tower and still in a non-touristy location with shops, cafes and tasty fruit stands. The rooms are a bit small, but that is normal in Paris. We'll definitely be back!

We first stayed here nearly 8 years ago and we’re very happy to return. Christine is so helpful and she encourages me to use my minimal French with maximum grace. She made our visit special as did this excellent property. I highly recommend it.

Our family booked 2 rooms for a long weekend. The entire staff was very friendly and helpful, the place was very clean, and the location was terrific—walking distance to the Eiffel Tower, the Seine, and the Arc de Triumph. Breakfast was very good, and the honor bar in the lobby was very convenient. We will return!

While the price is reasonable the location is great for the Eiffel Tower. The room was clean overall (excep the glass cups didn't smell good) and we had a view of the tower. Would use it again. One more thing about the location: the Passy covered market is within a wallking distance which is a great place to buy authentic cheese, bread, cured meat, fruits and such if you want to go out for picnic.

Room was Clean, spacious bathroom and comfortable bed. Breakfast avail for purchase if needed. Walking distance to Trocadéro and Eiffel Tower. Lady in check in was very nice and spoke English. I would return.

We have been coming to Hotel Passy for many years, and have always been very happy with the fores stay there. We knew the former where today it is the daughter who runs the hotel further in the same good evil and style. It's been the next 40 years since we were first there. Fantastic neighborhood and fantastic service.

This hotel was comfortable and perfectly located not far from the Eiffel Tower. There is a great boulangerie next door and other good restaurants nearby. Close to a pharmacy, an Orange store ( to get your SIM card ) and an ATM. Staff were friendly and helpful.

My girlfriend and I had a wonderful experience at Passy Hotel! The room we stayed in had amazing views of the Eiffel Tower, and the bustling street. The room was kept tidy and cleaned daily and the staff were friendly with any questions we had. Would definitely recommend to anyone.

My boyfriend and I were in Paris for the weekend and we stayed at the Passy Eiffel Hotel. The hotel was super stylish and is located on an ideal location. The breakfast was good and our room great for the weekend!

We visited Paris for a few days having never been before, so weren't sure what to expect. The hotel is lovely, stylish and clean. The staff were very friendly and helpful and you could see the Eiffel Tower from our room - which was lovely. The location is perfect - just a quick walk down to the River Seine and the Eiffel Tower. There are plenty of shops, bars and cafes. It's a perfect spot for families or couples visiting Paris.

Very Parisienne, very nice decor, very clean, helpful staff, very nice fresh breakfast with a good variety of food, around the corner from Trocadero with excellent views of the Eiffel Tower. In a very nice upmarket shopping street

Hairdryer wouldn’t work. We asked for a bigger room couldn’t get it. The receptionist wasn’t very helpful. No balcony in the room or air as there was a gate/railing outside window. Too expensive for very small room.

The hotel is situated in a very lovely area with lot of shops nearby and beautiful houses. When checking in the receptionist was not clear about breakfast not included in the price, which only came out when checking out. This was very disappointing that no one disclosed that to us. The hotels public areas were lovely decorated and nice, especially the small bar at the lobby. The room was very humid and we did not have a good view, there was a homeless person across the street and we had a room from the second floor so we heard a lot of commotion at night. Also as we were 2 friends traveling we wanted to have 2 blankets and it took 4 requests to get one for the other person which was quite frustrating. The glasses in the room were a bit dirty. Overall the hotel was OK but definitely would not go again with that price and no breakfast included. Was very exited from the pictures but not so much after this ordeal.

Great location that combines local life very close to tourism. lovely rooms, spacious, clean and quiet! the staff always smiling and helpful and the breakfast rich and tasty. I hope to return with my family to Paris and to this hotel again!!!

My wife and I had a great stay at the Hotel Passy Eiffel. The location is very good, near restaurants, and bakery shops and a metro station. Our room was small but comfortable and despite been on a busy road and on the first floor, we couldn't hear any noise from the road when the windows were closed. There was even a partial view to the Eiffel Tower! The hotel is charming and I recommend it.

This hotel was incredible and I really couldn’t fault it! The location is really nice and very safe, just a short distance from the Eiffel Tower with lots of nice cafes/restaurants around.

We’ve rebooked for the end of the year after only being back for two days.

We LOVE! Hotel Passy! It's small, quaint, clean, ideally located. The staff is super friendly and very helpful! Breakfast service is the perfect way to get your day started! We were particularly enchanted with the egg poacher! This was our first trip to Paris. The view of the Eiffel Tower was perfect! The elevator is super small. I think it's adorable. My guess is that the building is really old, just having it is a luxury accommodation! We relied on the front desk staff for dinner recommendations. Each of the three places was outstanding! Sad... VERY SAD! to be leaving!

Fantastic location... a short walk to the Eiffel Tower. Don't miss the wedding stairs on the way to the tower. They lead to a cute little neighborhood with nice shopping and restaurants with the most picture perfect view of the Eiffel tower. Hotel is small, quaint and perfectly French.

The hotel was very nice and clean. And the location was perfect! Just a 3 minute walk from the metro station and a 15 minute walk to the Eiffeltower. I really recommand this hotel if you want to stay in Paris!

We had a perfect stay at the passy hotel. It was just 2 minutes away from the Eiffel Tower. The service was excellent and really friendly. The check in was possible at 12 pm. We would defenetly come back!

Love this hotel; very convenient. Friendly and professional service.
I have used this place before and returned realizing how convenient place this is.
I recommend to my friends and colleagues if they don't need to stay in very expensive hotel.
